<div class="game-article-overview">
<h2>ABOUT DRIFT HUNTER</h2>
<p>Drift Hunters is a free-to-play, browser-based drifting game that puts you behind the wheel of cars like the Toyota AE86, Nissan S13, Toyota Supra, Ford Mustang, and even the RWB 911. It’s nowhere near as in-depth as your modern-day PC and console games, but you can tune and customize your car to an impressive level. Since it’s based on the UNITY engine, it does offer 3D graphics and the physics are somewhat realistic.</p>
<h2>HOW TO PLAY</h2>
<p>Gameplay is relatively simple. Use your keyboard’s <strong>ARROW KEYS</strong> to control the vehicle, the <strong>SPACEBAR</strong> to engage the handbrake, <strong>C</strong> to change the camera view. <strong>Left Shift</strong> and <strong>CTRL</strong> to upshift and downshift, respectively. While the handbrake is usually useful in games like this, you might find that you don’t need it as steering alone is usually enough to introduce a pretty wicked drift.</p>
<h3>Drifting</h3>
<p>In-game, the longer you drift, the more you earn point multiplier increases. You can utilize the points to purchase exotic cars like top performance <a href="https://www.topspeed.com/cars/porsche-911/ke282.html" class='_in'><strong>Porsche 911</strong> GT</a>. There’re 25+ completely customizable vehicles available to buy.</p>
<h3>Tuning</h3>
<p>Each car you purchase can be fully tuned, brake balance, turbo, rear offset, front camber, and many more. You can modify these features to find the best tuning for your drifts. Also, you can upgrade the car&#8217;s performance. The weight, turbo, weight, and the engine can be entirely upgraded with better parts.</p>
<h2>Drift Hunter full car list:</h2><ul class="spip"><li class="spip"> <a href="https://www.topspeed.com/cars/the-10-most-important-classic-japanese-cars-ar189046.html" class='_in'>Toyota Trueno GT-APEX (AE86)</a>- Datsun 240z</li><li class="spip"> Nissan 240sx (S13)</li><li class="spip"> BMW M3 (E29)</li><li class="spip"> Mitsubishi Evolution (VIII)</li><li class="spip"> Subaru Impreza WRZ</li><li class="spip"> BMW M3 (E36)</li><li class="spip"> Nissan 240sx (S14)</li><li class="spip"> Nissan Silvia Spec R (S15)</li><li class="spip"> <a href="https://www.topspeed.com/cars/honda/2006-honda-s2000-ar12172.html" class='_in'>Honda S2000</a> (AP1)</li><li class="spip"> Mazda RX-7 Type R (FD3S)</li><li class="spip"> <a href="https://www.topspeed.com/cars/bmw-m3/ke2366.html" class='_in'>BMW M3</a> (<a href="https://www.topspeed.com/cars/bmw/2001-2003-bmw-m3-e46-ar1376.html" class='_in'>E46</a>)</li><li class="spip"> <a href="https://www.topspeed.com/cars/toyota-gt86/ke4085.html" class='_in'>Toyota GT86</a></li><li class="spip"> Toyota Supra (JZA80)</li><li class="spip"> <a href="https://www.topspeed.com/cars/bmw/2012-bmw-1-series-m-coupe-ar98020.html" class='_in'>BMW 1M Coupé</a> (E82)</li><li class="spip"> Infiniti G35 Coupe</li><li class="spip"> Mercedes Benz AMG CLA Saloon (C45)</li><li class="spip"> Ford Fiesta ST (Mark VI)</li><li class="spip"> <a href="https://www.topspeed.com/cars/nissan/2009-2017-nissan-370z-ar117725.html" class='_in'>Nissan 370z Coupe</a></li><li class="spip"> Nissan Skyline GTR (R34)</li><li class="spip"> Lexus IS350</li><li class="spip"> Dodge Challenger Hellcat</li><li class="spip"> Ford Mustang Fastback (S550)</li><li class="spip"> BMW 335i (F30)</li><li class="spip"> <a href="https://www.topspeed.com/cars/nissan/2020-nissan-gt-r-nismo-driven-ar187537.html" class='_in'>Nissan GTR (R35)</a></li><li class="spip"> Porsche 911 GT (993)</li></ul><h2>Features</h2><ul class="spip"><li class="spip"> Ten different tracks to drift car</li><li class="spip"> 26 luxurious customizable vehicles</li><li class="spip"> Stunning 3D graphics that you can adjust easily in setting</li><li class="spip"> Ability to modify and tune every part of your vehicle</li></ul><h2>FAQ</h2>
<h3>What is the best car for drift hunters?</h3>
<p>When it comes to drifting, you will have to find the best car to suit your requirements. While some gamers are certain that the Nisan GTR is the best car in Drift Hunters, some had huge success with the Nisan Silvia Spec R.</p>
<h3>What is the name of the most expensive car in the Drift Hunters game?</h3>
<p>The priciest car to buy in the game is the Porsche 911 GT (993), but it is not the fastest.</p>
<h3>What is the fastest car on Drift Hunters?</h3>
<p>The fastest car in Drift Hunters is the Nissan GT-R (R35).</p>
<h3>Who invented Drift Hunter?</h3>
<p>The game was originaly developped by Ilya Kaminetsky. You can downlaod it directly from the developper on his <a href="https://studionum43.itch.io/drift-hunters/purchase" class='_out' rel='external nofollow noopener'>website</a> and you can also support the project financialy from there.</p>
<h2>Other Cool Games</h2>
<p>Check out our other drift games: <a href="https://www.topspeed.com/car-games/car-games/figure-8-drift-practice-ar186788.html" class='_in'>Figure 8</a>,
<a href="https://www.topspeed.com/car-games/car-games/madalin-stunt-cars-3-ar186757.html" class='_in'>Madalin Stunt Cars 3</a> and <a href="https://www.topspeed.com/car-games/car-games/topspeed-stunt-racing-ar186380.html" class='_in'>Topspeed Stunt Racing</a> for more awesome car game fun!</p>
